list.item:
New Nisa
is located about 1.5 km north-west of Old Nisa . The tell with a surface of about 25 ha is surrounded on all sides by powerful walls with a height up to 9 m. It has two entrances ( one from Bagyr village and one from the North West ) . In Parthian times , the city was divided into two parts , the upper city (
ark
) and the lower city (
shakhristan
) . The layout clearly indicates a densely populated town . The Parthian buildings are interpreted as remains of the fortress , burial houses and storehouses .
